SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 796
By Southerland
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Nash Rader of South
Greene High School on being named to the
TSWA 2A All-State football team.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Nash Rader of South Greene High School,
an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who has proven himself a formidable
competitor on the football field; and
WHEREAS, the Tennessee Sports Writers Association (TSWA) recently named Nash
Rader to the 2025 Class 2A All-State football team in recognition of his excellence on the
gridiron as a quarterback for South Greene High School; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Rader not only finished his senior year with 1,279 rushing yards for
twenty-two touchdowns and completed 45 of 89 passes for 868 yards and ten touchdowns, but
he also helped the South Greene Rebels to an 8-4 record and their first appearance in the
second round of the State playoffs since 2022; and
WHEREAS, no stranger to awards, Mr. Rader was duly named Region 1-2A Player of
the Year; and
WHEREAS, Nash Rader epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as he has
achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
field; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Rader's notable achievement is a source of great pride for his family,
especially his father, who was twice named All-State in the 1990s, as well as his community,
and his school; and
SJR0796
011740
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Nash Rader is a winner both on and off the field of play, and his dedication
to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect, admiration, and commendation of this General
Assembly; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Nash Rader of South
Greene High School on being named to the Tennessee Sports Writers Association's 2A All-
State football team, wishing him much success and happiness in his future endeavors.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
